    "timestamp": "2025-07-06T02:25:12.315481",
    "question": "How do I overcome anger and jealousy through spiritual practice?",
    "response": "Dear soul, cultivate equanimity by focusing on your own actions, not others'.  Jealousy and anger stem from attachment to outcomes.\n\nAs I teach in Bhagavad Gita 2.64: **प्रकाशं च प्रयच्छामि ज्ञानाग्निः सर्वकर्माणि** (*prakāśaṃ ca prayacchāmi jñānāgniḥ sarvakarmāṇi*) - I illuminate the path to wisdom; the fire of knowledge consumes all actions.\n\nLet the light of wisdom dispel the darkness of these emotions. May peace reside within you. 🕉️\n",
    "citations": [
